items.name: Legend of Korra Artstyle - LoHa
items.description:
Please check out my Ko-Fi page if you are interested in supporting me.

LoRA commissions open! -> Fiverr

No trigger words for V1.18! Just use the LoRA: <lora:legendOfKorrav118:0.7>

Note: trained on extracted frames from the entire series but I did not tag any characters in it. You might be able to generate specific characters if you prompt for them using booru tags.

Follow the steps in the Model Version notes to reproduce my images.

Sample images generated from Nothing.

All negative embeds should be easy to find. and Prompts should be included in the sample images! Click the little icon in the bottom right to see it.

It was trained on 558 512x512 images scraped from the internet and 18 epochs using animefull_final.

Danbooru tags generated by Waifu Diffusion 1.4 Tagger and fine tuned for specific tags.

modelVersions.name: v1.18
modelVersions.description:
Generate using a weight of 0.5-1 like this: <lora:legendOfKorrav118:0.7>


How I archived my generations:

  1. txt2img: DPM++ SDE Karras with 20 steps,512x512(can go up to 768 for wide or tall), Restore faces on (using CodeFormer weight 1.0 in Settings), Hires-fix on, to 1024x1024 (double original size) with your preferred upscaler and Denoise 0.5, CFG 7. Then send to img2img!

  2. img2img: DPM++ SED Karras with 20 steps, Restore faces on (CodeFormer weight 1), rescale to 1536x1536, CFG 7, Denoise between 0.3-0.7 (based on how much you want to improve the image), SAME PROMPT! Send to extras when happy with img2img/inpaint results.

  3. extras: Scale to x3 (final will be 4608x4608, I suggest going lower, I did x3 just for the samples here) Upscaler 1 - FatalAnime 4x, Upscaler 2 - SwinIR 4x with 0.10 visibility, GFPGAN 0.10 visibility, CodeFormer 0.10 visibility.

(worst quality, low quality, extra digits:1.4) or (worst quality, low quality:1.4)

just use hires fix as much as your video card is capable of, so as not to give an error, with 8gb of video memory it is 512x768 with hires fix 2-2.15, upscaler Latent (nearest-exact), the picture will be much more detailed. items.name: Bigby | The Wolf Among Us / Fables
items.description:
Character Lora of Bigby Wolf from The Wolf Among Us / Fables

"You think my job is easy? You try keeping a bunch of Fables from killing each other. How d'you think this all works? By being BIG and being Bad." -Bigby

The hero fabletown needs and deserves -soul3142


This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 International License.

If you want to, you can support me on Ko-fi or Patreon.

Main Trigger Word - bigbyTWAS_soul3142 , check examples for other ones.

RECOMMENDATIONS :-

Use LoRA name according to the downloaded file when copying example prompts.

  1. Highres Fix : Use if you are getting blurry and ugly images & try reducing LoRA weight

    My upscale method: txt2img 512x768 -> send to img2img -> controlnet tile upscale, tile diffusion 2x scale with 4xUltrasharp upscaler and tiled vae

  2. Weight: 0.5 - 0.7

  3. Clip Skip: 2

  4. Denoising : Don't go too high, it can alter a lot of details

  5. For better face's : use ADetailer

There are imperfections here & there, which i usually leave it in as is, (i never do any inpainting in examples), most of which like hands can be fixed with better prompting, negative embeddings while other like weapons are just bad majority of the time no matter the model as of today.

Some LoRA's are flexible with any clothing, some are not so keep these things in mind.

This is an unofficial fanmade LoRA, not intended for any commercial purpose and use. All characters and IP rights are owned by their respective creators and owners. I do not own rights to any of these characters.

items.name: SDXL_Nisney_V1 (Stable)
items.description:
Hi all !

Here is my brand new model SDXL_Nisney

SDXL_Nisney what is it?

It is a model trained on a few licenses from the famous Nisney studio. With for example Nino & Ntitch or Napunzel (and many others). It does both cartoon style and CGI.

A few tips for use:

-If you want a flat 2D cartoon style do not put in the prompt words like "detailed, realistic,...". "Masterpiece" works well, "high quality" too.
The best is to make a prompt only descriptive.

-For 3D CGI style, "highly detailed, realistic" works well

-A cfg scale between 4 and 8.5 works (I recommend 7)

-A minimum of 30 steps (I recommend minimum 36)

-Works great with Hires fix -Can work with Refiner. But I advise you not to put more than 5 or 6 steps. Beyond that, you risk losing style. (not recommended)

-Sampling method: DPM++ 2M SDE Karras or DPM++ 2M Karras

Have fun 😉

PS : I will make a stabilized version of the model as soon as possible

items.name: Au Ra FF14 - Concept
items.description:
BEFORE USING READ DESCRIPTION!

LoRA representing Au Ra from FF14.

Recommended weight - 1.

How to use:

Write the activation word - au ra.

Version 2.0

Now you can generate desired horns type by adding one of those to your prompt:

  • front horns, back horns, down horns, fin horns

If you get "bad" horns, you can add other types in negatives.

Tails were not separated by types in this version, they are just general tails atm.

In next update want to fix scales layered over clothes.

Example prompt:

black au ra, tail

gold au ra, front horns

white au ra, down horns

Version 1.0

About tails - they are generating sometimes and you need to set pretty high weight for prompts, if you have any advices how to improve this part, please write me.

What you can use in prompt (under each position you can find examples):

  • Color / material au ra - to set the color of features.

  • Thick / thin tail - to choose either thick or thin version of tail.

  • Smooth / pointed tail - to choose either smooth tail or pointed.

Example prompt:

black au ra, (tail:1.2), (thin tail), (smooth tail:1.3)

gold au ra

Yes, only activation words, no need to tag horns (yet).

Afterword

All preview images generated with highres fix, which is recommended for usage. Look at their metadata in case if you want to see what prompt actually does.

If you run in any problems during generation on realistic models, keep in mind, that this LoRA is trained in first place to work on anime models.

Works fine with style LoRAs that i use.

Please, leave a review and comment what could be improved / fixed.
